199
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:10,480
Kristi agreed and they parked by 
the side of the road for the night.

200
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:16,480
The next morning, there was no sign 
of Aron at Little Wild Horse Canyon.  

201
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:22,400
All they found was a truck from Colorado 
with a bike inside and skis on the roof.

202
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,720
'That's probably Aron's truck,' said Megan.  

203
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:31,840
'He must be in the canyon 
already. We've missed him again.'

204
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:37,840
She wrote their email addresses on a piece 
of paper and left it on the truck window.

205
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:45,040
'Why didn't we just get his phone number?' 
Megan asked as they drove back to Moab.
 
 

206
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,000
15 hrs 15 mins

207
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:56,800
12.00 am My headlamp is on and I'm chipping at the 
boulder. I've managed to chip a space above and  

208
00:21:56,800 --> 00:22:03,760
below an area of pink rock. Perhaps I can remove 
this large piece before I stop for the night.  

209
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:11,040
I will need to hit it hard. I don't want to 
break the knife, so I use a different part of  

210
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:18,080
the multi-tool. I hit the boulder as hard as I can 
and the piece of rock falls onto my trapped arm.  

211
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:26,000
I can now see some softer rock below. I chip at 
the rock for another hour and remove as much as  

212
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:32,400
the piece that came off before. More success, 
but my left arm hurts and I have to stop.

213
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:41,840
I take a sip of water. I have decided to do 
this every ninety minutes. I look up at the sky.  

214
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,200
It's a clear night and it's very cold.

215
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:54,640
Now that I've stopped chipping I feel cold. The 
wind is the worst. Every few minutes, it blows  

216
00:22:54,640 --> 00:23:01,920
down the canyon and makes my body shake. I decide 
to use my climbing bag as a jacket to keep warm.  

217
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:11,120
I lay everything inside it on top of the boulder. 
Then I put the bag back on. I'm a little warmer  

218
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:17,600
but I need something soft to put my legs 
on. I take my rope, form it into a circle,  

219
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:23,760
and lay it on a rock below me. Now I can rest 
my knees instead of standing up all the time.

220
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:28,960
After a while, I begin to 
feel uncomfortable again.  

221
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:36,160
The problem is the weight on my legs. I 
decide to try and build some kind of seat.  

222
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:43,360
I put on my harness and rope. Then I 
tie carabiners to one end of the rope  

223
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:49,840
and make a kind of ball. The idea is to throw 
the rope over one of the boulders above my head.  

224
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:56,320
If I do it right, the ball will stick in the 
space between the boulder and the canyon wall.

225
00:23:57,680 --> 00:24:01,600
It takes twenty-five throws before 
it lands in the right place.  

226
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:10,480
Now, will it hold my weight? I sit 
in the harness. It holds. Success!  

227
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:20,080
I feel very happy. But I'm not comfortable 
for long. I soon need to move again. I stand  

228
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:26,800
and chip for twenty minutes, then sit and rest 
for twenty minutes. This becomes my routine.

229
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:35,520
As morning comes, I'm not feeling too unhappy. 
This first night was not as bad as I thought.  

230
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:42,240
I've done quite well, but one thought still 
worries me: I haven't chipped much rock  

231
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:49,120
from the boulder. At this speed, it will 
take me 150 hours to free my trapped arm.

232
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:54,720
Chipping is not enough. I will 
have to think of something else.
 
 
 

233
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:56,720
CHAPTER FIVE

234
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:00,000
A sad message

235
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,920
23 hrs 30 mins

236
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:11,360
8.15 am I am feeling optimistic. The sun is 
shining into the canyon and a raven has just  

237
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:17,760
flown across the blue sky above my head. The 
sight and sound of the bird fills me with hope.

238
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:24,160
I hold my leg in the sunlight. 
It feels warm against my skin.  

239
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:33,600
But I need to do something. It's time for plan 
two. I will use my ropes, webbing and carabiners  

240
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:41,280
to try and lift the boulder and free my hand. I 
look up. There's a sharp piece of rock above my  

241
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:47,440
head. If I can throw the rope around this, it 
might hold everything in the right position.

242
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:55,840
After many tries, I finally succeed. I tie 
the other end of the rope around the boulder.  

243
00:25:56,560 --> 00:26:02,560
But when I pull, nothing happens. Everything 
holds, but the boulder doesn't move.  

244
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:09,840
I put more weight on the rope, but it still 
doesn't work. The rope is not tight enough.
 
 

245
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,040
28 hrs 15 mins

246
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:19,840
1.00 pm I've spent four hours trying to 
lift the boulder, but nothing has worked.

247
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:24,000
Suddenly, I hear voices.

248
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:27,280
'Help! Help!' I shout.

249
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:35,680
I stop and listen. At first, there's 
nothing. But then I hear a sound from above  

250
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:43,440
and realise my mistake. It's just a small animal 
moving in the rock. I'd imagined it was people.

251
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:47,760
The sound of my voice shouting 
for help frightened me.

252
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:54,480
It made me feel lost and alone. I make 
a promise that I won't do it again.  

253
00:26:55,520 --> 00:27:01,920
The optimistic feelings of earlier in the 
day have disappeared. No one is going to save  

254
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:08,960
me. That leaves only the third, and worst, 
plan: I will have to amputate my right arm.  

255
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:16,720
What will I need for the job? The knife, that's 
certain, but also a tourniquet to stop the blood.  

256
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:21,040
The plastic pipe from the 
CamelBak seems best for that.  

257
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:28,640
I take it off and use a carabiner to make it 
tight. It works well and I feel a bit better.

258
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:36,560
As soon as I put the knife against the 
skin of my arm, I feel ill. I can't do it.  

259
00:27:37,520 --> 00:27:43,120
It would be like killing myself. I drop 
the knife and lay my head on the boulder.  

260
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:51,120
None of my plans have worked. I can't 
free my hand. I can't lift the boulder.  

261
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:58,960
I can't amputate my arm. My only hope is 
rescue, but I'll die before help arrives.

262
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:06,560
I feel angry with the boulder, but it's not the 
boulder's fault - it's mine. Everything about  

263
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:13,760
this stupid adventure was a mistake. I didn't 
tell anyone where I was going, I didn't go with  

264
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:18,480
Kristi and Megan to the west canyon, and I 
didn't get off the boulder when it moved.
 
 

265
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:20,800
30 hrs

266
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:26,720
2.45 pm It's exactly twenty-four 
hours since the accident.

267
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:32,000
I decide it's time to film a 
message for my family and friends.  

268
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:37,360
I place my camcorder on the boulder, 
turn it on and start speaking.

269
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:47,520
'My name is Aron Ralston. It's just after 
three o'clock on Sunday, April the 27th, 2003.  

270
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:55,440
I have been trapped in Blue John Canyon for the 
last twenty-four hours. My parents are Donna and  

271
00:28:55,440 --> 00:29:03,600
Larry Ralston of Eaglewood, Colorado. If anyone 
finds this, please give it to them. Thank you.'

272
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:11,760
I describe all that has happened in the last 
two days. As I reach the end of my story,  

273
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:18,560
I feel very sad. I know this could be a final 
goodbye to my parents and sister, Sonja.

274
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:24,320
After telling them how much I love them, 
there is only one more thing to say.  

275
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:28,000
'Mum, Dad, Sonja - I'm sorry.'

276
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:34,640
I turn off the machine. All I can do 
now is wait for someone to find me.
 
 
 

277
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:36,880
CHAPTER SIX

278
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:38,560
Waiting

279
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:41,680
33 hrs 15 mins

280
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:52,720
6.00 pm My second night in the canyon is moving 
closer. Beyond that, I see no future. Escape has  

281
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:59,520
been impossible and I will die before anyone 
finds me. I feel strong enough to survive the  

282
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:08,320
fear of death, but not my body's need for water. 
This terrible, growing thirst will drive me crazy.

283
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:11,520
I now have only a quarter 
of a litre of water left.  

284
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:20,560
I have to make this last as long as possible. I 
drank at 3.15 pm, just after I finished filming.  

285
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:25,280
Then I missed the next drink and 
decided to save it for later.  

286
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:32,320
I'll drink at nine, midnight, three and six in 
the morning, but I'll take even smaller sips.

287
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:39,120
The mosquitoes have found me. There are 
several at my feet and some drinking the  

288
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:44,800
blood on the canyon wall. I kill five 
or six as they circle around my head.  

289
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:51,920
Can I eat them, I wonder? Even if I could, 
it wouldn't be enough to keep me alive.

290
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:58,160
I go back to waiting. It seems 
colder than the night before.  

291
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:02,000
I start chipping at the 
boulder just to keep warm.
 
 

292
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:05,200
36 hrs 15 mins

293
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:09,120
9.00 pm Night has fallen.  

294
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:16,160
The mosquitoes have gone. The sky above 
is beautiful: clear with bright stars.  

295
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:23,440
But clear skies mean lower temperatures. I 
must do something to cover more of my body.

296
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:32,160
I tie the camera bag around my left arm. Then 
I tie webbing around my right arm and put  

297
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:38,160
rope around each of my legs. I do the 
same for my right arm, using webbing.

298
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:45,840
I put rope round each leg. It looks 
funny and I can't help smiling.

299
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:53,200
I begin my routine of standing and sitting. 
Most of my body feels warmer, but I'm still  

300
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:59,840
shaking because my head and neck are cold. I 
decide to put the plastic rope bag over my head.  

301
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:04,000
I keep the far end open to let fresh air in.  

302
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:10,960
I lay my head against the boulder. I 
still can't sleep but at least I'm warmer.

303
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:15,920
The long, boring hours of 
the night pass slowly by.  

304
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:25,040
Finally, the sky grows lighter. Today, it's a 
dirty white colour. I wonder if this is cloud.  

305
00:32:26,080 --> 00:32:31,120
Clouds at night are good because they trap the 
day's heat in the canyon, but clouds during  

306
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:37,280
the day are bad because the sun doesn't warm 
the air. There's also the chance of a storm.

307
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:41,840
Slowly the pale sky turns bright blue.  

308
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:48,960
It's going to be hot again. As always, the 
light and warm air make me want to do something.  

309
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:56,080
I try and lift the boulder again by 
pushing down on the rope with my feet.

310
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:59,520
This doesn't work either and 
I feel suddenly hopeless.  

311
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:07,680
What more can I do? No voice inside 
my head suggests anything useful. All  

312
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:12,320
I see in my mind are pictures of the food 
and drink left on the floor of my truck.

313
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:19,600
I think again about amputating my arm. 
I didn't try hard enough the last time.  

314
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:24,160
I need to be brave and try again.

315
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:26,640
I put on the tourniquet and make it tight.  

316
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:32,960
When everything is ready, I try to cut through 
the skin of my arm with the longer knife.  

317
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:41,200
I push hard but the skin doesn't break. 
Then, over the same area, I use the shorter,  

318
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:48,160
sharper knife. But even that doesn't work. 
It's still not sharp enough to do the job.

319
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:53,360
All I have for the time I've 
spent on this is a long red line  

320
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:58,720
across my right arm. I take off the 
tourniquet and go back to waiting.
 
 

321
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:01,760
47 hrs 30 mins

322
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:12,640
8.15 am The raven appears. I check my watch. It 
has arrived at exactly the same time as yesterday.

323
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:16,400
For the first time in two days,  

324
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:22,880
I need to urinate. I open my shorts and watch 
the yellow urine disappear into the sand.

325
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:27,360
I spend most of the day chipping, resting,  

326
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:30,320
and counting the minutes before 
my next drink of water.
 
 

327
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:33,840
54 hrs

328
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:39,040
2.45 pm It's the middle of the 
afternoon and time to film again.  

329
00:34:40,160 --> 00:34:46,000
Filming has now become a part of my 
daily routine. I turn on the camcorder.

330
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:54,480
'Hi, everyone. It's Monday, April 
the 28th. I'm still trapped.  

331
00:34:55,440 --> 00:35:01,440
I've been here for exactly forty-eight 
hours. That's two whole days with no  

332
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:06,960
sleep and very little water. I now have 
only about one-eighth of a litre left.'

333
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:16,080
I continue with a message to my sister, Sonja. 
She is getting married in the autumn. I tell  

334
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:20,080
her how proud I am of her and 
send her my love and best wishes.

335
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:28,720
I finish filming at 3.35 pm. It's strange 
but I feel the need to urinate again.  

336
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:33,840
This time, my second voice tells 
me not to urinate on the ground.

337
00:35:35,360 --> 00:35:39,520
Save it, Aron. It will soon 
be all you have to drink.

338
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:44,720
It's good advice. I urinate into the CamelBak.  

339
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:53,600
The urine is now a dark orange colour. The 
other urine was clearer. Why didn't I save it?
 
 

340
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:57,840
57 hrs 15 mins

341
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:05,680
6.00 pm It's early evening. Sunlight shines 
off the bottom of thin clouds high above me.  

342
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:12,160
I hope they will stay and keep the 
heat in the canyon. But as time passes,  

343
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:20,720
it seems to grow colder. My water won't last much 
longer. Soon, I will have to start drinking urine.

344
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:27,920
Like the raven, the mosquitoes seem 
to arrive on time. I kill a few more.  

345
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:34,000
Mosquitoes mean there must be water quite 
close - probably at the Big Drop Rappel.

346
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:39,840
Forget it, Aron. You'll never see water again.

347
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:44,320
The first voice is back. I try not to listen.

348
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:46,560
