374
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:19,280
at least forty-eight hours before the 
police will start a search and rescue  

375
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:24,640
operation. This meant that they wouldn't 
do anything until late the following day.
 
 

376
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:28,640
63 Mrs 15 mins

377
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:35,600
12.00 am It's my third night here and I've 
decided to take my first sip of urine.  

378
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:40,400
There's still half a cup of water 
left, but I want to save it.

379
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:45,600
The urine tastes bad, but not 
quite as bad as I thought.  

380
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:54,000
I decide not to drink any more until the water is 
finished. I've changed my drinking routine because  

381
00:39:54,000 --> 00:40:01,040
the night is colder. I can now only sit for a 
few minutes so I take smaller sips every hour.
 
 

382
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:04,640
66 hrs 15 mins

383
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:09,840
3.00 am It's now sixty hours since my accident.  

384
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:14,960
That's sixty hours of pain, no 
sleep, and very little water.

385
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:23,120
Two hours later, it's time for my next sip of 
water. I put the bottle between my legs and  

386
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:31,520
turn the top. When it's open, I try and lift it 
towards my mouth. But it hits my harness and falls  

387
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:39,760
back onto my legs. I am too tired to catch it. 
