00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:52,080
Now look what you've done! Says the first voice.

390
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:57,760
I know exactly what I've done. I've 
just lost half of the rest of my life.
 
 

391
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:00,000
70 hrs

392
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:10,320
6.45 am As morning arrives once more, I feel a 
little hope. At least I've survived another night.  

393
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:16,800
It's now Tuesday, April the 29th: 
my fourth day trapped in the canyon.

394
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:23,600
I decide to film earlier today. I 
put the camcorder on the boulder,  

395
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:29,120
then turn the screen the other way. I 
don't want to look at myself as I speak.

396
00:41:30,640 --> 00:41:37,520
'Hi. It's Tuesday morning. I guess 
everyone missed me when I didn't arrive  

397
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:43,440
for Leona's party last night. Most people 
will probably think I'm still travelling.  

398
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:50,080
Except for Brion. When I don't arrive 
for work, he'll think something is wrong.  

399
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:57,600
He might call the police and report me missing. 
They'll wait forty-eight hours before searching.  

400
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:04,560
If I'm lucky, they'll start some time 
on Wednesday. If I'm very lucky, they  

401
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:11,440
might search the Robbers Roost area first. Even 
then, the earliest they'll reach me is Thursday.  

402
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:18,640
I'll try to stay alive as long as I can, but I 
can't imagine living longer than one more day.  

403
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:27,920
This means help will arrive too late. By Thursday, 
I'll be dead. And this video will be history.'
 
 
 

404
00:42:29,600 --> 00:42:30,480
CHAPTER EIGHT

405
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,240
The raven

406
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:35,440
70 hrs 45 mins

407
00:42:37,600 --> 00:42:44,640
7.30 am That last video recording was the 
most pessimistic so far. It's strange,  

408
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:51,360
but the feeling of hopelessness doesn't last. 
As the sky grows brighter, I think of the raven.  

409
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:57,840
The bird is a sign of hope. Just thinking 
about it makes me want to do something.

410
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:06,240
I try lifting the boulder once more. I make 
the rope even shorter, but when I step on it,  

411
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:13,760
nothing happens. I do everything I can to 
make it work. I push, jump and shout as I  

412
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:20,880
put all my weight onto the rope. It's still no 
good. The boulder doesn't move a millimetre.

413
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:30,400
I step down and lay my head on the boulder. I feel 
like crying but I can't. There's not enough water  

414
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:40,000
in my body to produce any tears. But there's still 
the knife. It's lying open on top of the boulder.

415
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:42,320
Suddenly, I know what I'm going to do.  

416
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:49,840
Quickly, I put the tourniquet around my arm 
and tighten it. Then I pick up the multi-tool,  

417
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:57,520
open the shorter knife and push it hard into my 
arm. This time, the knife goes all the way in.

418
00:43:58,960 --> 00:44:03,040
I pull out the knife and look at the 
deep hole I've made in my right arm.  

419
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:11,680
I can't believe I've done this. It didn't even 
hurt and there's very little blood. I can see the  

420
00:44:11,680 --> 00:44:18,320
bones in my arm through the hole. I will never be 
able to cut through them with only a small knife.

421
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:26,240
It's time for a drink. I pick up the bottle and 
feel the last of the water disappear down my  

422
00:44:26,240 --> 00:44:34,480
throat. I check the time. It's exactly 8.00 
am and all I have to drink now is urine.
 
 

423
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:38,080
71 hrs 45 mins

424
00:44:39,840 --> 00:44:45,520
8.30 am The raven appears. It's 
fifteen minutes late but I'm happy.  

425
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:52,640
I was beginning to think it wouldn't come. I feel 
happy and start thinking of all the wonderful  

426
00:44:52,640 --> 00:44:59,920
times I've spent with friends and family. I 
remember a trip to Washington D.C. with my sister,  

427
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:05,600
and another to Gettysburg with my dad. 
I also think of all the adventures I've  

428
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:12,240
had with different friends. The time passes 
quickly Midday arrives without me realising.

429
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:20,240
I urinate into the CamelBak. Then I pour the 
clearer half of the urine into my water bottle.  

430
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:28,160
I throw the rest away. I have no idea how 
long anyone can survive on urine alone.  

431
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:32,320
At least drinking it wasn't as bad as I expected.

432
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:39,280
It is now the warmest part of the day. 
This is the time I am most comfortable.  

433
00:45:40,320 --> 00:45:44,320
I have found the best way to sit 
and feel calmer in the warm air.  

434
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:51,680
Perhaps help will arrive in time. If 
so, I will soon be as free as the raven.

435
00:45:53,120 --> 00:46:00,000
Three hours later, I have reached the end of my 
third day trapped in the canyon. None of my plans  

436
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:06,480
of escape have worked. All I can do is stay 
strong for another night and hope for rescue.

437
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:16,400
I eat the last burrito. It is too dry to get down 
my throat so I take a mouthful of urine. The urine  

438
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:21,840
tastes better at night because it's colder, 
but it's still going to be a long, hard night.  

439
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:28,320
On Wednesday morning, Brion After was 
at work in the shop. At nine-fifteen,  

440
00:46:28,960 --> 00:46:35,120
he called Leona to check if he had arrived, 
but he hadn't. Brion had waited long enough.

441
00:46:36,480 --> 00:46:42,240
He picked up the phone. Aron's 
mother answered on the first ring.

442
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:43,120
'Mrs Ralston?'

443
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:44,720
'Yes?'

444
00:46:46,240 --> 00:46:49,520
'This is Brion After - Aron's 
boss at Ute Mountaineer.  

445
00:46:50,480 --> 00:46:56,800
I'm afraid I'm rather worried about him. He 
hasn't returned from a trip he took last week.  

446
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:03,520
Do you know where he went? No one here 
has seen him since last Wednesday.'

447
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:09,840
'Oh dear,' said Aron's mother. 
'I have no idea where he is.

448
00:47:11,040 --> 00:47:14,960
I called him last week and left a 
message, but he didn't call back.  

449
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:19,040
Did he tell any of his 
housemates where he was going?'

450
00:47:20,640 --> 00:47:26,480
'No, just that he might hike somewhere in the 
Canyonlands area of Utah,' explained Brion

451
00:47:27,440 --> 00:47:29,760
'I think you should call the Aspen police.'

452
00:47:30,880 --> 00:47:35,600
'Yes, I'll do that right now. 
I'll let you know what happens.'

453
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:38,400
'Thank you, Brion.'

454
00:47:39,440 --> 00:47:47,600
Mrs Ralston's hand was shaking as she put down 
the phone. She suddenly had an idea. Perhaps  

455
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:51,840
Aron had sent an email to one of his 
friends saying where he was going?

456
00:47:53,280 --> 00:48:00,960
She went to the computer. Aron had an email 
address - but what was it? She found his name,  

457
00:48:00,960 --> 00:48:07,760
but had to answer a secret question to read 
his emails. None of the answers she gave worked  

458
00:48:07,760 --> 00:48:14,720
but she kept trying. In the end, she guessed the 
correct answer and sent the information to Brion.

459
00:48:16,160 --> 00:48:22,640
After Brion had called the Aspen police, the 
head officer, Adam Crider, started the rescue  

460
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:28,320
operation. He called Mrs Ralston for the 
license-plate number of her son's truck.  

461
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:35,840
Mrs Ralston had written it down on a piece 
of paper. When she read it to Officer Crider,  

462
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:42,000
she didn't realise it was wrong. Aron had 
given it to her in a hurry and made a mistake.

463
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:49,280
Officer Crider called back and told Mrs Ralston 
there was no record of that license plate.  

464
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:56,000
This left her with another problem. How could 
she find the correct license-plate number?

465
00:48:57,440 --> 00:49:03,760
Brion After was having better luck. He had 
found a list of email addresses for Aron's  

466
00:49:03,760 --> 00:49:10,800
climbing friends. Perhaps they knew where 
he was. He wanted to check immediately,  

467
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:16,320
but he had to leave for Australia that 
day. He called Aron's housemate Elliot  

468
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:23,200
and asked him to manage the store and rescue 
operation until he returned. Elliot agreed.

469
00:49:24,640 --> 00:49:30,960
When Elliot reached the store, he received 
a call from Mrs Ralston. She wanted to check  

470
00:49:30,960 --> 00:49:35,920
the license-plate number she had 
given Brion. It was on his desk.  

471
00:49:36,960 --> 00:49:39,120
Elliot checked as she read out the number.

472
00:49:40,560 --> 00:49:45,360
'Wait. Did you say 886, Mrs Ralston?'

473
00:49:46,560 --> 00:49:46,880
'Yes.'

474
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:53,120
'Brion made a mistake. He wrote down 888.  

475
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:57,840
I'll call Officer Crider and 
give him the correct number.'

476
00:49:58,880 --> 00:50:03,840
By early afternoon, Elliot had 
received an email from Steve Pratchett,  

477
00:50:03,840 --> 00:50:09,680
the most important of Aron's climbing 
friends. Steve had climbed for many years.  

478
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:18,800
He often led rescue operations to find climbers 
lost in the mountains. Another friend, Jason,  

479
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:23,920
had sent Steve a list of all the canyons 
Aron said he wanted to hike in Canyonlands.  

480
00:50:25,120 --> 00:50:30,160
Steve called the Utah police for the 
area and spoke to one the main officers,  

481
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:37,280
Kyle Ekker. Officer Ekker was very helpful. 
Steve gave him the latest license-plate  

482
00:50:37,280 --> 00:50:41,680
number for Aron's truck and Officer 
Ekker sent his men out to look for it.

483
00:50:43,440 --> 00:50:50,960
They returned as night fell. There was no sign of 
the truck. Officer Ekker checked the number with  

484
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:58,880
the national license office. There was no vehicle 
on record. Once again, the number was wrong.

485
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:02,480
The bad news reached Aron's mother.  

486
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:09,120
Then she remembered that Aron was living in 
Albuquerque, New Mexico, when he bought the truck.  

487
00:51:10,160 --> 00:51:16,800
The vehicle license office for the area was in 
Santa Fe. She called and an officer searched  

488
00:51:16,800 --> 00:51:26,080
the records and found Aron's name. The records 
showed his license-plate number as NM 846-MMY.

489
00:51:27,840 --> 00:51:33,520
Finally, they had the correct number. The 
information was given to Officer Ekker.  

490
00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:40,480
It was too late to continue searching that 
night. It would have to wait until the morning.

491
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:48,000
'Wait for us, Aron,' Mrs Ralston said 
as she went to bed. 'We're coming.'
 
 

492
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:51,120
89 hrs 15 mins

493
00:51:52,640 --> 00:52:00,480
2.00 am The darkness seems unreal. In fact, I 
don't know what is real and what isn't anymore.  

494
00:52:01,600 --> 00:52:07,840
I start to have visions. Friends suddenly 
appear in the canyon like silent ghosts  

495
00:52:07,840 --> 00:52:14,320
and wave me towards them. I follow and find 
myself in some place I know from the past.  

496
00:52:15,360 --> 00:52:22,640
They smile at me in a kind way, but they never 
speak. Because of their kindness, I am not afraid.  

497
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:30,240
I know they are protecting me. I am 
happy while the visions last. To me,  

498
00:52:30,240 --> 00:52:37,200
they are real. It is only when they disappear and 
the cold and pain return that I know they are not.  

499
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:46,000
Then, shaking hard, I continue chipping at the 
boulder. After that, I sit again and it's not long  

500
00:52:46,000 --> 00:52:53,280
before the visions return. During the second half 
of the night, I have visions of myself as a child.  

501
00:52:55,120 --> 00:52:58,240
Sometimes I'm playing cards with my grandfather.  

502
00:52:59,280 --> 00:53:03,440
Other times I am running across 
bright green fields with my friends.

503
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:09,920
Something about the visions tells me that I 
have not given the people I care about enough  

504
00:53:09,920 --> 00:53:16,400
attention. I'm always thinking of the things I 
want to achieve and not noticing other people.  

505
00:53:17,520 --> 00:53:22,800
Now I realise that my love for friends and 
family is the main reason I want to escape.  

506
00:53:23,840 --> 00:53:29,280
The thought of seeing them again is 
keeping me alive. I promise myself that  

507
00:53:29,280 --> 00:53:33,760
if I can escape from here back to the 
people, I will be kinder towards them.

508
00:53:35,120 --> 00:53:42,080
The visions always include some kind of drink. 
It is usually something cold and sweet like apple  

509
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:50,800
juice or ice tea. Just as I am about to drink, the 
vision disappears and I wake up. Then I feel the  

510
00:53:50,800 --> 00:53:58,080
cold and the pain of the rope against my legs. 
I stand up and begin my routine all over again.

511
00:53:59,520 --> 00:54:03,600
However, the visions tell me 
something: I am not ready to die.  

512
00:54:04,640 --> 00:54:09,840
As morning comes on the fifth day, I feel 
sure I can still last a few more days.  

513
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:18,240
I don't know if this is true, but I'm still 
alive when the sun rises. The raven appears on  

514
00:54:18,240 --> 00:54:26,080
time. The sound of its wings and the light in the 
canyon are beautiful. I watch its smooth flight,  

515
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:32,320
following the line of the canyon. I take out my 
camera and film as it disappears from view.
 
 
 

516
00:54:33,760 --> 00:54:34,560
CHAPTER NINE

517
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:36,480
'It's his truck'

518
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:39,920
97 hrs 45 mins

519
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:49,200
10.30 am I don't want to look at my watch. When 
I did this last night, the time seemed to pass  

520
00:54:49,200 --> 00:54:58,800
more slowly. I have a new idea. It came to me, as 
I was looking at all the rocks around me. Why not  

521
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:06,240
find a hard rock and use it to break the boulder? 
There's one in a hole in the canyon wall above me.  

522
00:55:06,240 --> 00:55:14,000
It is round and black. I reach up and pull it out. 
It's perfect - just the right size and weight.

523
00:55:15,680 --> 00:55:21,360
I hit the rock hard against the boulder. 
Little bits of stone fly into the air.  

524
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:28,720
It's working. I continue, but soon have to 
stop because of the pain in my left hand.  

525
00:55:29,840 --> 00:55:31,760
I decide to rest for a while.

526
00:55:33,280 --> 00:55:40,240
Early afternoon is usually the warmest time 
of day. But today it's only thirteen degrees,  

527
00:55:40,240 --> 00:55:46,000
the coldest day so far. It also means 
that tonight will be the coldest night.  

528
00:55:47,200 --> 00:55:50,960
Realising this makes me want to do 
something while it's still light.

529
00:55:52,480 --> 00:55:57,920
The problem with using the black rock 
was that it hurt my left hand. But what  

530
00:55:57,920 --> 00:56:05,520
if I tie a sock around my hand to protect 
it? I do this and it works. By 6.00 pm,  

531
00:56:06,240 --> 00:56:12,320
I have taken off more of the boulder in three 
hours than I did in four days. But it's still  

532
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:18,320
not enough. And even with the sock there is 
too much pain in my left hand to continue.

533
00:56:19,680 --> 00:56:25,520
I put down the rock. I feel sure I won't 
survive another night in the canyon.  

534
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:31,920
I finally accept this. There is 
nothing else I can do to save myself.
 
 

535
00:56:33,120 --> 00:56:35,760
110 hrs 15 mins

536
00:56:37,280 --> 00:56:44,800
11.00 pm The canyon feels as cold as ice. 
I have been awake for over a hundred hours.  

537
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:52,400
Another night of the sitting - standing routine 
will kill me. I haven't had any clean water since  

538
00:56:52,400 --> 00:57:00,240
eight o'clock yesterday morning, only urine. How 
much longer can I survive? Death could come at  

539
00:57:00,240 --> 00:57:06,880
any moment. I am so certain of this that I take 
the knife and write the dates of my life on the  

540
00:57:06,880 --> 00:57:14,960
canyon wall. When I have finished I read them by 
the light of my headlamp: ARON OCT 75 - APR 03.

541
00:57:16,640 --> 00:57:22,800
Around midnight, I have another vision. I 
am walking alone through the canyon wall.  

542
00:57:23,920 --> 00:57:29,040
On the other side is a living room. 
I step inside and look around.  

543
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:36,000
A little boy in a red shirt comes into 
the room. I guess he must be about three.  

544
00:57:37,280 --> 00:57:43,680
Suddenly, I know who he is. He is my future 
son and the room is in my future home.  

545
00:57:44,800 --> 00:57:51,040
The little boy runs across the wooden floor, 
laughing. I pick him up with my left arm.  

546
00:57:52,080 --> 00:57:58,480
My right arm has no hand. Then I put him 
onto my shoulder and he laughs even more.  

547
00:57:59,520 --> 00:58:04,000
He holds my arms in his little hands 
and together we dance around the room.  

548
00:58:05,120 --> 00:58:08,960
The sun is shining and I 
feel free, happy, and alive.

549
00:58:10,720 --> 00:58:17,360
The vision disappears. I am back in the canyon 
again, but now I don't feel the same as before.  

550
00:58:18,560 --> 00:58:22,480
Seeing the boy has changed everything. Now,  

551
00:58:22,480 --> 00:58:27,520
even with the cold, pain, tiredness 
and thirst, I am sure I will survive.

552
00:58:29,200 --> 00:58:34,480
On Thursday, May the 1st, Kyle Ekker 
was looking at a map of the Canyonlands  

553
00:58:34,480 --> 00:58:42,400
area on his office wall. The clock above 
read 9.07 am. Already that morning,  

554
00:58:42,400 --> 00:58:46,560
his men had searched the top and 
centre of the area and found nothing.

555
00:58:48,000 --> 00:58:53,440
What about the Robbers Roost canyons 
in the south? The only roads down there  

556
00:58:53,440 --> 00:59:00,720
were made of rocks and sand. It might take 
longer to search. He called Glen Sherrill,  

557
00:59:00,720 --> 00:59:07,200
the head officer for the area. When Glen 
answered the phone, Kyle described Aron's truck.

558
00:59:08,560 --> 00:59:14,800
'It's a red Toyota. License number NM 846-MMY.'

559
00:59:16,080 --> 00:59:19,200
'I think I've seen a truck 
like that,' Glen replied.  

560
00:59:20,240 --> 00:59:23,360
'I'll radio one of my men and ask them to check.'

561
00:59:24,560 --> 00:59:26,720
Kyle thanked him and put down the phone.

562
00:59:28,160 --> 00:59:32,640
Twenty minutes later, Glen 
called back. 'Officer Kyle?'

563
00:59:33,840 --> 00:59:34,400
'Speaking.'

564
00:59:35,520 --> 00:59:39,920
'Glen Sherrill here. We've found 
the truck you're looking for.  

565
00:59:41,040 --> 00:59:43,120
It's in the Horseshoe Canyon carpark.'

566
00:59:44,640 --> 00:59:51,760
By 10.00 am, the good news had reached 
Elliot, Steve, and Mrs Ralston. Steve  

567
00:59:51,760 --> 00:59:56,640
immediately arranged for a rescue team to 
join the police and help in the search.  

568
00:59:57,840 --> 01:00:03,120
Half an hour later, they were on their 
way. Things were now moving fast.
 
 
 

569
01:00:04,960 --> 01:00:05,680
CHAPTER TEN

570
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:07,360
Escape

571
01:00:08,560 --> 01:00:10,320
120 hrs

572
01:00:12,160 --> 01:00:20,640
8.45 am It's Thursday, May the 1st. 120 
hours without sleep. Two days without  

573
01:00:20,640 --> 01:00:27,840
water. I can't believe I'm still alive. I 
didn't think I'd survive beyond Wednesday.  

574
01:00:29,040 --> 01:00:32,560
Perhaps the vision of the little 
boy kept me alive last night.  

575
01:00:33,680 --> 01:00:38,400
But now, with no sign of a rescue, 
my hopes are disappearing fast.

576
01:00:39,760 --> 01:00:43,040
I am also upset because the raven hasn't appeared.  

577
01:00:44,080 --> 01:00:50,480
It's never been this late before. I try and 
forget about the bird and pick up the camcorder.  

578
01:00:51,360 --> 01:00:56,320
I am certain that this will be 
my last message to my family.

579
01:00:56,320 --> 01:01:00,240
I am calm as I leave necessary 
instructions for my parents.

580
01:01:01,760 --> 01:01:04,480
I tell them to give most of my things to Sonja.  

581
01:01:05,600 --> 01:01:12,960
Then I tell them what to do with my dead body. The 
video ends with three simple words: 'I love you.'

582
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:17,760
I'm crying as I close the 
camcorder for the last time.  

583
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:22,240
But there are no tears - my 
body is too dry for tears.

584
01:01:23,760 --> 01:01:31,120
Now I can only wait. I can't accept this. I've 
discovered that nothing I can do will help me  

585
01:01:31,120 --> 01:01:38,240
escape. But it's better to be doing something than 
nothing. I pick up the black rock and hit it as  

586
01:01:38,240 --> 01:01:44,640
hard as I can against the boulder. I continue, 
trying to forget the pain in my left hand.  

587
01:01:45,760 --> 01:01:52,160
In the end, I can't. I try to drop the 
rock, but the fingers of my hand won't open.

588
01:01:53,600 --> 01:01:57,280
What have you done now? asks the first voice.

589
01:01:58,480 --> 01:02:00,320
Stay calm, says the second.

590
01:02:01,440 --> 01:02:05,840
Slowly, my fingers loosen and 
the stone falls out of my hand.  

591
01:02:06,400 --> 01:02:10,560
I look at my other arm. It's 
covered with bits of rock.

592
01:02:12,080 --> 01:02:16,800
As I'm removing these with the knife 
I push too hard and the blade goes  

593
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:24,000
through the skin near my wrist. I don't feel 
anything. That part of my arm must be dead.  

594
01:02:25,120 --> 01:02:32,000
My right hand died long ago. It's now 
a dark blue colour. I push the knife  

595
01:02:32,000 --> 01:02:38,480
through the skin of my thumb. There's a sound 
as some gas escapes, followed by a bad smell.

596
01:02:39,920 --> 01:02:46,400
The arm is poisoned and the poison will kill me. 
I don't want the arm to be a part of me anymore.  

597
01:02:47,440 --> 01:02:54,160
I throw myself against the boulder. When I look 
at my arm, I see that it's in a strange position.

598
01:02:55,600 --> 01:03:02,720
That moment is like the sun coming out. 
I realise what it means. I can break my  

599
01:03:02,720 --> 01:03:08,480
arm by using my own weight. That means I 
won't have to cut through bone anymore.  

600
01:03:09,600 --> 01:03:16,880
I throw the whole weight of my body below the 
boulder. There is a loud noise. I keep going.  

601
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:24,720
There is a second loud noise. I've done 
it! I've broken both bones in my arm.

602
01:03:26,160 --> 01:03:29,840
I tie the tourniquet, take 
the knife and begin cutting.

603
01:03:30,720 --> 01:03:34,560
The only thing on my mind is 
escape, but the pain is terrible.

604
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:38,000
I scream as I push down with the knife.

605
01:03:39,600 --> 01:03:43,840
For almost one hour the pain, 
screams, and cutting continue.
 
 

606
01:03:44,880 --> 01:03:48,080
122 hrs 47 mins

607
01:03:49,600 --> 01:03:55,520
11.32 am Finally, I feel the knife 
hit rock on the other side of my arm.  

608
01:03:56,480 --> 01:03:59,680
I fall back with a single thought 
screaming through my head.

609
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:06,800
You've done it, Aron! You're FREE! FREE! FREE!

610
01:04:08,240 --> 01:04:13,440
There's no time to lose. Blood is 
coming out of the end of my arm  

611
01:04:13,440 --> 01:04:15,520
and it's a long walk back to my truck.

612
01:04:16,880 --> 01:04:22,640
I tighten the tourniquet. Then I tie 
my climbing bag on my arm to hold it.  

613
01:04:23,680 --> 01:04:29,600
I tighten it around my neck and put 
my things inside. Before I leave,  

614
01:04:29,600 --> 01:04:36,160
I take two pictures of the part of my arm still 
trapped by the boulder. Now I am ready to go.

615
01:04:37,600 --> 01:04:46,800
I can't walk straight. My body crashes from one 
side of the canyon wall to the other. I stop. My  

616
01:04:46,800 --> 01:04:56,640
heart is going much too fast. I could still die at 
any moment. I make myself stay calm. What I need  

617
01:04:56,640 --> 01:05:03,280
most of all is water. There might be some at the 
Big Drop Rappel, but first I need to get there.

618
01:05:04,640 --> 01:05:09,440
It takes me twenty minutes. I 
stand at the edge and look down.  

619
01:05:10,480 --> 01:05:13,680
It is just over eighteen 
metres to the canyon floor.

620
01:05:15,120 --> 01:05:22,320
There are metal rings in the rock for climbers. 
I tie my rope to them and rappel down.  

621
01:05:22,320 --> 01:05:29,360
With only one arm, this is not easy. For 
once, I am careful as I go down the rope.  

622
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:37,840
I reach the bottom and turn. On the ground in 
front of me is a pool of brown water. It's full  

623
01:05:37,840 --> 01:05:44,800
of dead mosquitoes but I don't care. I fill my 
bottle and drink one litre in a few seconds.  

624
01:05:46,000 --> 01:05:52,320
I drink another and don't want to move. I just 
want to stay there for the rest of my life.

625
01:05:54,400 --> 01:06:00,240
That won't be long if you don't start walking. 
There are still twelve kilometres to go.

626
01:06:01,760 --> 01:06:09,600
The voice is right. I drink one more litre, 
slowly this time. Then I fill my bottle and  

627
01:06:09,600 --> 01:06:15,280
the CamelBak and begin walking. Blood 
is coming out faster from my arm now.  

628
01:06:16,320 --> 01:06:19,120
I wonder if I can get back to the truck in time.

629
01:06:20,720 --> 01:06:28,880
Things start to go wrong. I get lost up a side 
canyon and have to turn round. Then I notice that  

630
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:36,720
water is coming out of my CamelBak. There's a hole 
in it. Quickly, I drink the rest of the water.  

631
01:06:37,760 --> 01:06:44,240
Now I only have the water in the water bottle. 
This has to last all the way back to the truck  

632
01:06:44,240 --> 01:06:50,800
and the temperature is rising. I am so weak 
and tired I can't imagine surviving that long.  

633
01:06:51,840 --> 01:06:57,360
I take a sip and keep the water in my 
mouth as I walk. That seems to help.

634
01:06:59,120 --> 01:07:01,840
I still wonder if I can get back to my truck.  

635
01:07:02,960 --> 01:07:09,440
I can't walk straight, I can't think for more 
than a few seconds, and I'm losing blood, fast.
 
 

636
01:07:10,560 --> 01:07:13,840
125 hrs 10 mins

637
01:07:15,440 --> 01:07:18,880
1.55 pm I've arrived at the Great Gallery.  

638
01:07:19,920 --> 01:07:25,520
The paintings are amazing but all I can 
think of is water. There is more here.

639
01:07:26,880 --> 01:07:32,960
I stop to fill the water bottle. It has 
taken me two and a half hours to travel  

640
01:07:32,960 --> 01:07:41,280
six kilometres. For someone close to death I have 
done well. But my problems are getting worse every  

641
01:07:41,280 --> 01:07:48,240
minute. Blood is now coming from my arm really 
fast and I'm in terrible pain from the amputation.  

642
01:07:49,280 --> 01:07:53,840
I want to stop and rest, 
but I can't. I must go on.

643
01:07:55,200 --> 01:08:01,840
I walk as fast as I can. By two-thirty, 
I have covered nearly ten kilometres.  

644
01:08:02,960 --> 01:08:07,680
Only three more kilometres to my truck, 
but I'm feeling weaker every minute.
 
 

645
01:08:08,880 --> 01:08:12,160
125 hrs 45 mins

646
01:08:13,920 --> 01:08:20,800
2.30 pm I've come to another huge canyon. 
The walls must be over thirty metres high.  

647
01:08:21,840 --> 01:08:29,600
Ahead of me is a steep hill. This is bad news. 
I'll never be able to climb it - I'm too weak.  

648
01:08:30,800 --> 01:08:38,080
Something makes me look again. I shake 
my head, unable to believe what I see.

649
01:08:38,080 --> 01:08:42,400
About seventy metres ahead of me are 
a family of three people - a man,  

650
01:08:42,400 --> 01:08:46,720
a woman and a young boy. They 
are walking away from me.

651
01:08:47,760 --> 01:08:52,800
'HELP! HELP! PLEASE! I NEED HELP!'

652
01:08:54,080 --> 01:08:56,400
They turn and come running towards me.

653
01:08:57,920 --> 01:09:05,200
When they reach me, I begin telling my story: 
'My name is Aron Ralston. I was trapped by a  

654
01:09:05,200 --> 01:09:12,160
boulder in the canyon for five days. This 
morning, I had to amputate my arm to escape.  

655
01:09:13,200 --> 01:09:21,120
I need a doctor. I'm losing blood, fast...' 
Unable to continue, I fall to the ground.

656
01:09:22,480 --> 01:09:28,720
The man gives me a bottle of water. 'The police 
at the carpark told us about you,' he says.

657
01:09:30,160 --> 01:09:37,920
His name is Eric. His wife is Monique and his 
son is called Andy. They are tourists from the  

658
01:09:37,920 --> 01:09:44,080
Netherlands. Eric gives me more water while 
Monique and Andy run back to get the police.  

659
01:09:45,280 --> 01:09:50,160
After about ten minutes, Eric helps 
me up and we continue walking slowly.

660
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:58,000
The steep trail is ahead. Even with Eric's 
help, I know I won't be able to climb it.  

661
01:09:59,040 --> 01:10:03,040
'How will I ever get out 
of here?' I ask myself.
 
 
 

662
01:10:04,160 --> 01:10:05,040
CHAPTER ELEVEN

663
01:10:06,240 --> 01:10:08,400
127 hours

664
01:10:09,680 --> 01:10:12,640
126 hrs 18 mins

665
01:10:14,240 --> 01:10:20,800
3.03 pm A noise somewhere above me 
answers the question. It's a helicopter!  

666
01:10:21,760 --> 01:10:28,400
A helicopter to take me to hospital. I 
can't believe it! It doesn't seem real.  

667
01:10:29,440 --> 01:10:34,080
I sit down and wait as a man jumps 
to the ground and walks towards me.

668
01:10:35,360 --> 01:10:37,840
'Are you Aron Ralston?' he asks.

669
01:10:38,960 --> 01:10:39,280
'Yes.'

670
01:10:40,400 --> 01:10:44,000
A second man gets out of the 
helicopter and they help me  

671
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:50,720
inside. I ask one of the men to get 
my climbing bag. Eric gives it to him.

672
01:10:52,320 --> 01:10:56,320
'Thank you, Eric,' I say. 'Thanks for everything.'  

673
01:10:57,360 --> 01:11:00,880
I wave goodbye as the 
helicopter rises into the air.

674
01:11:01,840 --> 01:11:06,240
I sit behind the pilot and watch 
blood pour slowly down my arm.

675
01:11:07,600 --> 01:11:12,320
Be strong, Aron. You're almost safe.

676
01:11:12,320 --> 01:11:15,360
'Keep him talking,' the pilot says to his partner.

677
01:11:16,480 --> 01:11:20,000
'Where are we going?' I ask the second man.

678
01:11:21,120 --> 01:11:25,920
'We're taking you to the 
hospital in Moab,' he replies.

679
01:11:25,920 --> 01:11:27,200
'How long will that take?'

680
01:11:28,240 --> 01:11:30,240
'It's about twelve minutes from here.'

681
01:11:31,680 --> 01:11:35,920
He asks me what happened in the 
canyon and I begin telling my story.  

682
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:44,800
By the time I finish, we are circling around Moab. 
I look down and see an area of green grass below.

683
01:11:46,320 --> 01:11:54,000
This gets bigger as we move down towards it. I 
realise we are landing in front of the hospital.  

684
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:58,400
A man who looks like a policeman is 
standing with two nurses in white  

685
01:11:58,400 --> 01:12:04,640
coats on the hospital steps. The helicopter 
lands and the nurses carry me into the building.

686
01:12:06,000 --> 01:12:11,440
They put me in an empty room. The 
man walks in and introduces himself.  

687
01:12:12,640 --> 01:12:17,120
'Hi, Aron. I'm Steve, and I'm a Park Ranger.'

688
01:12:18,400 --> 01:12:24,080
As the nurses take off my shoes, I ask 
Steve to let my mother know that I'm OK  

689
01:12:24,640 --> 01:12:29,120
and to arrange for someone to collect all 
the things I left at Horseshoe Canyon.

690
01:12:30,400 --> 01:12:33,680
'I'll do that when we've 
finished here,' Steve replies.

691
01:12:35,120 --> 01:12:43,360
He wants to know what happened in the canyon. Once 
again, I tell my story. It's the third time I've  

692
01:12:43,360 --> 01:12:50,640
done this in two hours. When I finish, I can see 
that Steve wants to ask me a lot of questions.

693
01:12:52,080 --> 01:12:57,920
He doesn't get the chance. A doctor comes 
back into the room with a large needle.

694
01:12:59,280 --> 01:13:04,320
'Wait!' I say as she goes to put it into my skin.  

695
01:13:04,320 --> 01:13:11,760
'I have a problem with needles. I sometimes 
go into shock. I fell out of a chair once.'

696
01:13:13,120 --> 01:13:17,840
The doctor looks surprised. 'You 
mean you're not in shock already?'

697
01:13:18,640 --> 01:13:20,400
'I don't know,' I reply.

698
01:13:21,600 --> 01:13:23,840
'Look, do you want this for the pain or not?'

699
01:13:25,280 --> 01:13:32,800
'Damn it, yes!' I say. I continue talking 
to Steve as the needle goes into my arm.
 
 

700
01:13:34,000 --> 01:13:36,160
127 hrs

701
01:13:38,080 --> 01:13:41,840
3.45 pm I suddenly hear another man's voice.  

702
01:13:43,040 --> 01:13:49,840
He sounds like a doctor. He pulls at the things 
over my right arm and asks Steve what they are.

703
01:13:51,280 --> 01:13:54,800
'There are a couple of tourniquets 
under there,' Steve replies.

704
01:13:56,080 --> 01:14:00,720
'No, just one,' I whisper. I 
look at the clock on the wall.

705
01:14:02,160 --> 01:14:09,200
It's 3.45 pm on Thursday, May the 
1st. I realise that my nightmare  

706
01:14:09,200 --> 01:14:17,840
has lasted for exactly 127 hours. It's my last 
thought before falling into a long, deep sleep.
 
 

707
01:14:18,880 --> 01:14:19,520
EPILOGUE

708
01:14:20,960 --> 01:14:27,680
My rescue was only the first part of a long, 
difficult fight back to health. In that first  

709
01:14:27,680 --> 01:14:34,240
month, I had five operations. I was also 
taking eighteen different medicines a day.  

710
01:14:35,440 --> 01:14:42,400
Most were for the pain and to fight the poison in 
my blood. While I was taking them, I couldn't do  

711
01:14:42,400 --> 01:14:50,560
anything well. I couldn't sleep and my thoughts 
were unclear. After ten days in hospital, I went  

712
01:14:50,560 --> 01:14:57,600
home. A week later, I was back in hospital in 
Denver for my fifth and most difficult operation.  

713
01:14:58,640 --> 01:15:05,840
The time I woke up after the operation was the 
lowest point after my escape. I felt terrible.  

714
01:15:06,880 --> 01:15:10,800
I couldn't eat, I couldn't 
sleep and I was still in pain.  

715
01:15:11,920 --> 01:15:19,040
Later, I discovered that I nearly died. 
However by May the 25th, I was home to stay.

716
01:15:20,800 --> 01:15:26,400
The following weeks were difficult for 
my family. I was like a child again,  

717
01:15:26,400 --> 01:15:34,000
unable to do anything for myself. Slowly, 
however, things got better. I was soon eating  

718
01:15:34,000 --> 01:15:39,360
normal food and by the end of the summer, I 
was the same weight as before the accident.

719
01:15:40,800 --> 01:15:50,000
By this time, I had a prosthetic arm. I learnt 
to use it quite well. I felt pleased. It wouldn't  

720
01:15:50,000 --> 01:15:56,720
be long before I would be able to go climbing 
again. Of course, I didn't tell my mother that.

721
01:15:58,160 --> 01:16:05,040
On August the 31st, four months after the 
accident, I spoke at Sonja's wedding. Four  

722
01:16:05,040 --> 01:16:09,920
days later, I climbed Mount Moran 
in Wyoming with eight of my friends.

723
01:16:11,360 --> 01:16:16,720
On October the 25th - two days before 
my twenty-eighth birthday - I returned  

724
01:16:16,720 --> 01:16:22,080
to Blue John Canyon. Some friends, 
including Kristi Moore, were with me.  

725
01:16:23,120 --> 01:16:25,600
We filmed the place where the accident happened.  

726
01:16:26,800 --> 01:16:32,400
Then, as the others made their way back to their 
vehicles, I stayed behind for a few minutes.  

727
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:38,160
Just before I left, I looked at the 
dates of my life on the canyon wall.  

728
01:16:39,120 --> 01:16:48,080
I was wrong. My life didn't end in the canyon. 
Thoughts of the people I love had kept me alive.  

729
01:16:48,080 --> 01:16:56,640
If I wanted to see them again, I had to survive. 
That's what I told myself. And that's what I did.

730
01:16:58,480 --> 01:17:04,640
My accident changed my life. I know that 
even if I could travel back in time,  

731
01:17:04,640 --> 01:17:11,200
I wouldn't change anything. I would still say 
goodbye to Megan and Kristi and continue alone.  

732
01:17:12,320 --> 01:17:18,160
I've learned a lot from that choice. I believe 
we are on Earth to do the things we love,  

733
01:17:18,720 --> 01:17:24,800
even if that means making a hard choice. 
Sometimes, that means cutting out something  

734
01:17:24,800 --> 01:17:31,640
and leaving it in the past. Saying goodbye to 
things from our past is also a new beginning.
 
 
 
 

735
01:17:31,640 --> 01:17:33,172
- THE END -

